-- China sovereign fund names banker as executive vice president
-- 
-- Mon Jun 30, 2014 12:20AM EDT
-- None



BEIJING, June 30 (Reuters) - China Investment Corp., China's $575-billion sovereign wealth fund, said it has appointed a career banker as its new executive vice president.

Liu Guiping will be one of five executive vice presidents at CIC [CIC.UL], the fund said in a short announcement on its website. A former banker at Agricultural Bank of China <601288.SS>, China's fourth-biggest bank, Liu oversaw the retail banking business.  The website said Liu, who turns 48 this year, has a Ph.D. in economics.